MAC Address filtering allows you to collate a list of known devices that are allowed to connect to your WiFi network. The idea of this is that you are able to choose who connects to your network or other information for how that connected device can be used on the network. The implementation of 4G networks has come with many advantages over time and one of these is the quick download of files over a wireless network. This was a great step up from 3G which the download speed being almost 10 times better on 4G. Along with this comes the higher quality of voice and sound files that can be downloaded which makes using 4G almost as good as some internet connections in certain cases. These phones can also be used as hotspots which allows you to share out some of your data connection to others so they can also connect to the internet. This comes at a great advantage to others you may be working with as you can become fully connected together and get your work done much quicker together. \
